{"name": "openlock", "metadata": {"name": "openlock", "version": "1.2.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A Python locking library not depending on inter-process locking primitives in the OS", "upload_time": 1734025927}, "documentation": ["# openlock\n\nA locking library not depending on inter-process locking primitives in the OS.\n\nConsider a simple situation where multiple processes with the same working directory are trying to access a shared resource.\n\nCreate the lock.\n\n```python\nl = FileLock()\n```\n\nAcquire the lock.\n\n```python\nl.acquire()\n```\n\nRelease the lock.\n\n```python\nl.release()\n```\n\nAlternatively we may use the context manager protocol.\n\n```python\n  with FileLock():\n    ...\n```\n\nThat's it!\n\nFor comprehensive documentation about `openlock` see [https://www.cantate.be/openlock](https://www.cantate.be/openlock) (canonical reference) or [https://openlock.readthedocs.io](https://openlock.readthedocs.io).\n"], "modules": [{"name": "openlock", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "openlock.__version__", "xref": {"fqname": "openlock.openlock.__version__", "project": null}}, {"name": "openlock.Defaults", "xref": {"fqname": "openlock.openlock.Defaults", "project": null}}, {"name": "openlock.FileLock", "xref": {"fqname": "openlock.openlock.FileLock", "project": null}}, {"name": "openlock.get_defaults", "xref": {"fqname": "openlock.openlock.get_defaults", "project": null}}, {"name": "openlock.InvalidLockFile", "xref": {"fqname": "openlock.openlock.InvalidLockFile", "project": null}}, {"name": "openlock.InvalidOption", "xref": {"fqname": "openlock.openlock.InvalidOption", "project": null}}, {"name": "openlock.InvalidRelease", "xref": {"fqname": "openlock.openlock.InvalidRelease", "project":